{
  "texts": [
    "First, we utilize likelihood (or the reciprocal of perplexity (Chen et al., 1998)).",
    "This approach, however, is confined to LLM APIs that grant access to the predicted token distribution.",
    "Subsequently, we adopt the verbalized uncertainty strategy posited by Lin et al. (2022).",
    "Post-generation of the output y i, we prompt the LLM to articulate its uncertainty, either as words or as numbers, with the prompts listed in Table 4 in the Appendix.",
    "The optimal selection of specific perturbation and aggregation methods may vary depending on the dataset and LLM in use."
  ]
}